{"word":"πολίτης","slug":"πολίτης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πολίτης</b></el> <el>(πολί¯της, ου, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> also <a href='S:πολιήτης'><el>πολιήτης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a member of a city</i> or <i>state</i> (<el>πόλις</el>), <i>a citizen, freeman</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>civis</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>civis, a fellow-citizen</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><el>θεοὶ πολῖται  πολιοῦχοι</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}